recruiting_advice:
Focus on candidates that have a strong Data background - either as a product analyst or via a data science degree&#x20;



Watch for candidates from a services role - push to make sure they have experience in building analytics.



Ideal candidate will have exp building and maintaining a data pipeline.&#x20;

We're looking for candidates who have been successful DTC brands off the ground from noteworthy companies like Tend or Peachy. We're less interested in product marketing or B2B marketing backgrounds.

* We strongly prefer candidates that have built recognizable, unique and successful brands at venture-backed startups. One idea for looking for examples of these types brands could be to find top creative agencies in a city like NYC (e.g., Red Antler) and looking at their portfolio of work.&#x20;
* A creative, data-driven and scrappy Marketing Manager would be an ideal candidate for us. We're looking for a candidate to be hands-on as we are a small team, so it would be important that this teammate be self-sufficient in driving projects from start to end.

Hey! We're looking for a Software Engineer to join our team at Axle as our second hire (first engineering). We look forward to seeing the awesome candidates you find and would love to provide the below background information!&#x20;

We are a close-knit team and love bringing in phenomenal people. Talent is one thing, but we believe in building a company full of good people.&#x20;

Our product is an extensive platform, as they call a "compound startup", so that means we always have a ton to build and want a energetic and hard working person to build like crazy with us.&#x20;

We want someone that wants to truly understand the users and the industry and be very product focused. It is a very complicated space with a lot of user types and interconnected products (both technical and financial).&#x20;

We're working to modernize an archaic and problematic industry on Wall Street, so we have a really exciting customer base that includes investment banks and hedge funds. We want someone that is excited to be working on capital markets technology!

We're looking for a full stack engineer but definitely would consider primarily back end or front end engineers.&#x20;

**When reaching out to/screening candidates**:



Please **do not** proactively share the salary details in the first outreach. **it is ok to mention that we pay on top of the market and offer equity + sign on bonus**. For more detailed information on compensation please suggest they speak to recruiter.



1\. Check if candidates are really interested in working for a high growth company&#x20;

2\. Check on their English capability. We require at least business level of English as they will be working with US HQ on a daily basis&#x20;

3\. Growth minded person who is interested to work for a foreign company&#x20;
